description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for your next challenge?&lt;br /&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at the University Hospital of Wales for an experienced and motivated radiographer to join our multidisciplinary team. This is a busy and friendly department and we are looking for a Band 6 Radiographer to rotate through the 3 Philips cardiac catheter theatres. There will be a shift system in operation to include weekend working and on call.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will have high personal and professional standards and constantly strive to deliver the highest quality service and patient care. Experience in this field is essential, but training will be provided in some of the more specialised procedures. Sufficient post qualification experience is desirable and applications are invited from both external and internal candidates .&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Penny Lloyd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Superintendent Radiographer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Penny.lloyd@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02920743041&lt;/p&gt;
